WEBVTT

1
00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:56.807
[sheriff] We do not know why we are here.

2
00:01:05.649 --> 00:01:08.569
<i>We do not know who built the Silo.</i>

3
00:01:18.870 --> 00:01:24.376
<i>We do not know why everything
outside the Silo is as it is.</i>

4
00:01:25.710 --> 00:01:26.920
Good morning. Sheriff.

5
00:01:27.795 --> 00:01:30.132
Hey. Sam. You awake yet?

6
00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:32.801
[Sam] I'm about halfway there.

7
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:42.769
[sheriff] We do not know
when it will be safe to go outside.

8
00:01:45.771 --> 00:01:47.149
<i>We only know that day...</i>

9
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:51.736
<i>is not this day.</i>

10
00:02:28.064 --> 00:02:29.042
Hey.

11
00:02:29.066 --> 00:02:30.126
You're in early.

12
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:33.295
[deputy] Yeah. I couldn't sleep.
Got the damn leg cramps.

13
00:02:33.319 --> 00:02:35.507
When you get your coffee.
meet me in holding 3.

14
00:02:35.531 --> 00:02:36.656
Three?

15
00:03:13.651 --> 00:03:15.027
You want some coffee?

16
00:03:17.948 --> 00:03:19.259
[deputy] What are you doing?

17
00:03:19.283 --> 00:03:20.533
[sheriff] I wanna see her.

18
00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:22.661
[deputy] No. Sheriff.

19
00:03:23.245 --> 00:03:27.349
I should've done it three years ago.
But I couldn't listen.

20
00:03:27.373 --> 00:03:29.126
[deputy] Hey. Stop.

21
00:03:30.544 --> 00:03:34.965
[stammers] Come on out of there.
Let's talk about this.

22
00:03:36.800 --> 00:03:38.593
I made up my mind.
or I wouldn't be in here.

23
00:03:39.635 --> 00:03:40.846
I'm sorry. Sam.

24
00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:45.200
You're gonna say this to me
after all we've been through?

25
00:03:45.224 --> 00:03:46.828
Want me to wait till Sandy gets in?

26
00:03:46.852 --> 00:03:49.562
I don't want you to say it.

27
00:03:51.606 --> 00:03:54.836
Please. Sheriff. Don't say it.

28
00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:56.295
- Deputy Marnes...
- Please. Sheriff.

29
00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:57.528
I wanna go out.

30
00:04:01.491 --> 00:04:03.409
[sighs. sniffs]

31
00:04:04.243 --> 00:04:06.955
[breathes shakily]

32
00:04:07.497 --> 00:04:08.807
[exhales shakily]

33
00:04:08.831 --> 00:04:11.335
While you get things rolling.
I think I'm gonna lie down.

34
00:06:17.877 --> 00:06:19.105
[sheriff's wife] Are you getting coffee?

35
00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:20.355
[sheriff] I am. I am!

36
00:06:20.379 --> 00:06:24.009
Okay. I'll take milk. please.
Actually. no milk. I don't... I don't...

37
00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:26.278
I don't need any milk. No.

38
00:06:26.302 --> 00:06:28.180
- Come on. It's almost 8:00.
- Okay.

39
00:06:28.721 --> 00:06:30.762
- [sheriff's wife] Please.
- [sheriff] Okay. coming.

40
00:06:30.973 --> 00:06:33.393
[sighs] Thanks. [chuckles]

41
00:06:34.519 --> 00:06:36.122
[sighs] I don't know why we're doing this.

42
00:06:36.146 --> 00:06:38.582
We're not gonna get it.
We had two tries.

43
00:06:38.606 --> 00:06:39.691
[computer chimes]

44
00:06:48.449 --> 00:06:50.619
[chuckling]

45
00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:54.014
I can't believe it. [sighs]

46
00:06:54.038 --> 00:06:55.641
- [chuckles]
- Third time's a charm.

47
00:06:55.665 --> 00:06:57.685
You're just excited to have sex every day.

48
00:06:57.709 --> 00:06:59.521
Hey. you could be pregnant
a month from now.

49
00:06:59.545 --> 00:07:01.754
- Please let it be more than that.
- [chuckles]

50
00:07:04.216 --> 00:07:05.300
[sheriff's wife sighs]

51
00:07:06.134 --> 00:07:07.718
You know I love you no matter what.

52
00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:10.930
Shut up. We're doing this. Let's go.

53
00:07:11.682 --> 00:07:14.076
Allie.
his office doesn't open for an hour.

54
00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:15.829
Yeah. Well. we can get some breakfast.

55
00:07:15.853 --> 00:07:17.413
We can talk about baby names.

56
00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:20.165
Which will be me just humoring you.
because obviously.

57
00:07:20.189 --> 00:07:22.209
if I'm giving birth
to this little critter.

58
00:07:22.233 --> 00:07:24.170
I'm naming it whatever the hell I want.

59
00:07:24.194 --> 00:07:26.422
[chuckles] Okay.

60
00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:27.822
[Allison chuckles]

61
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.584
- Good luck.
- Oh. thanks. [chuckles]

62
00:07:40.334 --> 00:07:42.146
- Congratulations.
- [sheriff] Yeah. Thank you.

63
00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:43.338
Thanks. [chuckles]

64
00:07:45.507 --> 00:07:46.776
- Hi.
- [people murmuring]

65
00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:48.343
Oh. hi. Congrats.

66
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:51.012
Hi.

67
00:07:54.725 --> 00:07:56.577
I really hate this part.

68
00:07:56.601 --> 00:07:58.245
People are just happy for us.

69
00:07:58.269 --> 00:08:01.398
Oh. I just wish everyone didn't know.
[chuckles]

70
00:08:03.024 --> 00:08:04.002
Oh. shit.

71
00:08:04.026 --> 00:08:06.211
Sheriff. Mrs. Becker.

72
00:08:06.235 --> 00:08:08.380
I... [stammers. sighs]
I don't mean to intrude. [chuckles]

73
00:08:08.404 --> 00:08:09.488
So don't.

74
00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:12.718
There's your famous
tell-it-like-it-is manner.

75
00:08:12.742 --> 00:08:13.887
Why everyone likes you.

76
00:08:13.911 --> 00:08:15.954
If everyone likes me.
I'm not doing my job.

77
00:08:17.915 --> 00:08:21.310
Mrs. Becker. your husband might not be
interested in what I have to say...

78
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:22.728
What I'd be really interested in

79
00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:24.898
- is you leaving us alone. Gloria.
- Holston.

80
00:08:24.922 --> 00:08:27.233
But whatever our sheriff
may have told you.

81
00:08:27.257 --> 00:08:29.026
I provide fertility counseling...

82
00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:30.737
Oh. yeah? Like what?

83
00:08:30.761 --> 00:08:33.114
[chuckles] Your husband's waiting for me
to say something

84
00:08:33.138 --> 00:08:35.240
I'm not legally allowed to say.

85
00:08:35.264 --> 00:08:37.619
- Such as?
- Clever.

86
00:08:37.643 --> 00:08:40.729
[Gloria] I have no desire to be sent out.
Thank you. Sheriff.

87
00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:45.859
Mrs. Becker. if you have an open mind.
come see me.

88
00:08:47.610 --> 00:08:49.071
I wish you both the very best.

89
00:08:52.282 --> 00:08:53.634
What does she do exactly?

90
00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:56.011
She goes right to the edge
of promising people a baby

91
00:08:56.036 --> 00:08:59.121
if they do what she says. which is fraud.
And it's cruel.

92
00:09:07.673 --> 00:09:09.048
[doctor] I'll let that go numb.

93
00:09:10.801 --> 00:09:16.490
Now. after I remove the birth control.
it'll take two to three weeks

94
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:17.975
for your hormones to reset.

95
00:09:18.517 --> 00:09:20.702
Now. that said. some couples
do become pregnant

96
00:09:20.726 --> 00:09:22.205
within days of getting clearance.

97
00:09:22.229 --> 00:09:23.998
But then. you know all this.

98
00:09:24.022 --> 00:09:25.857
Is this your. uh... your second time?

99
00:09:26.732 --> 00:09:28.150
- Third.
- And last.

100
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:30.320
I'm almost thirty-eigh... eight.

101
00:09:33.197 --> 00:09:34.283
Can you feel this?

102
00:09:35.075 --> 00:09:36.260
Just pressure.

103
00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:40.455
[doctor] Well. even though you're numb.
it's still gonna feel weird.

104
00:09:41.038 --> 00:09:43.917
We make sure
the capsule's implanted quite deep

105
00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:47.187
so it never gives you any trouble.

106
00:09:47.211 --> 00:09:48.523
[grunts]

107
00:09:48.547 --> 00:09:52.842
- But not for long. as I am done.
- [grunts]

108
00:09:54.177 --> 00:09:55.196
And there it is.

109
00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:57.639
- [Allison sighs]
- You are no longer under birth control.

110
00:10:00.893 --> 00:10:02.703
[doctor] You are now free to make a baby.

111
00:10:02.727 --> 00:10:03.937
[Allison chuckles]

112
00:10:05.022 --> 00:10:08.024
[chattering. singing]

113
00:10:14.530 --> 00:10:16.509
Thank you. Mrs. Flores.

114
00:10:16.533 --> 00:10:20.513
I swear if one more person
congratulates us... [breathes heavily]

115
00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:22.182
Impregnate me. Now.

116
00:10:22.206 --> 00:10:24.893
- Yes. ma'am. [grunts. chuckles]
- [chuckles]

117
00:10:24.917 --> 00:10:27.061
- Wait. wait. wait. wait. wait. Wait. wait.
- Mmm. What?

118
00:10:27.085 --> 00:10:28.770
[sighs] Remember last time?

119
00:10:28.794 --> 00:10:31.356
At some point.
this is gonna start feeling like work.

120
00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:33.258
- Best work ever.
- [chuckles]

121
00:10:41.557 --> 00:10:44.453
[IT worker] We tried. like. four times
before we finally got clearance.

122
00:10:44.477 --> 00:10:45.746
so now's your time.

123
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:46.855
[Allison] Yeah. let's hope.

124
00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:48.582
[IT worker chuckles] My cousin Charlene.

125
00:10:48.606 --> 00:10:52.086
she convinced her husband
he had to dye his unit blue.

126
00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:53.171
Did it work?

127
00:10:53.195 --> 00:10:54.379
- They got pregnant.
- [chuckles]

128
00:10:54.403 --> 00:10:57.509
But I'm sure his blue dick
had nothing to do with it.

129
00:10:57.533 --> 00:11:00.470
She was just fucking with him.
Gives you a clue to that marriage.

130
00:11:00.494 --> 00:11:02.764
- Hello. Bernard.
- Morning. Bernard.

131
00:11:02.788 --> 00:11:04.498
Karen. Allison.

132
00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:07.559
[clicks tongue]
I see you posted an article

133
00:11:07.583 --> 00:11:10.772
on our BBS about recovering deleted files.

134
00:11:10.796 --> 00:11:13.399
- I did.
- You do know you need to get my approval

135
00:11:13.423 --> 00:11:16.318
for any IT-related content
before it goes wide.

136
00:11:16.342 --> 00:11:19.364
Well. I figured we could cut down
on service calls

137
00:11:19.388 --> 00:11:21.615
if people could handle
some things on their own.

138
00:11:21.639 --> 00:11:25.370
[chuckles] Hmm. I took it down. Your post.

139
00:11:25.394 --> 00:11:28.413
I have no doubt your intentions were good.

140
00:11:28.437 --> 00:11:31.875
but our reporting structure
is there for a reason.

141
00:11:31.899 --> 00:11:33.150
- Got it.
- Hmm.

142
00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:36.572
[whispers] Fucking asshole.

143
00:11:37.114 --> 00:11:38.758
Did you know you were breaking the rules?

144
00:11:38.782 --> 00:11:43.161
No. Maybe. Kind of.

145
00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:46.307
There's too many rules.

146
00:11:46.331 --> 00:11:47.767
Well. you wanted to work in IT.

147
00:11:47.790 --> 00:11:50.711
It's not just IT. It's everywhere.

148
00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:56.150
We blame the rebels
for erasing our history. right?

149
00:11:56.174 --> 00:11:57.402
Yes.

150
00:11:57.426 --> 00:12:00.154
So why can't we ask questions
about that stuff?

151
00:12:00.178 --> 00:12:04.533
And if losing our history is so bad.
why can some goons from Judicial

152
00:12:04.557 --> 00:12:05.909
send you down to the mines

153
00:12:05.933 --> 00:12:08.037
if you happen to have a relic
from the before times?

154
00:12:08.061 --> 00:12:09.145
Allison.

155
00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:12.000
Really?

156
00:12:12.024 --> 00:12:14.150
You're gonna use
your sheriff voice with me?

157
00:12:14.902 --> 00:12:17.613
Honey.
the Pact is the only history we have.

158
00:12:19.030 --> 00:12:21.759
What if a bunch of rule-breakers
decide they wanna see for themselves

159
00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:22.868
what it's like aboveground?

160
00:12:23.451 --> 00:12:26.538
They somehow manage to open that door.
we are done.

161
00:12:27.914 --> 00:12:30.292
Part of my job
is making sure that doesn't happen.

162
00:12:55.399 --> 00:12:57.193
[Allison sighs. sniffs]

163
00:13:03.991 --> 00:13:05.677
[breathes deeply]

164
00:13:05.701 --> 00:13:06.787
I got my period.

165
00:13:07.913 --> 00:13:10.249
I know. I know. We still have time.

166
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:18.149
[Marnes] What are you so afraid of?

167
00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:21.778
I'm afraid some drunken. pyromaniac
adolescent with a cherry bomb

168
00:13:21.802 --> 00:13:24.679
is gonna start a fire
that sets off a stampede.

169
00:13:25.681 --> 00:13:27.826
Are you done? Is it safe for me to speak?

170
00:13:27.850 --> 00:13:30.119
Since you've been wearing the sash
and we've been wearing a badge.

171
00:13:30.143 --> 00:13:33.664
Freedom Day has gone off without a hitch.
And that's a long damn time.

172
00:13:33.688 --> 00:13:35.290
All deputies will be on patrol.

173
00:13:35.315 --> 00:13:37.442
and we'll have fire teams
on every tenth level.

174
00:13:40.111 --> 00:13:42.841
[silo leader] It's getting harder to see
with every passing month.

175
00:13:42.865 --> 00:13:45.658
A long time between cleanings
means things are going well.

176
00:13:46.326 --> 00:13:47.619
No one wants a cleaning.

177
00:13:49.037 --> 00:13:51.331
but people need to see
what it's like out there.

178
00:14:03.427 --> 00:14:04.403
- Mrs. Becker.
- Oh.

179
00:14:04.427 --> 00:14:06.013
- Hi.
- I was looking for you.

180
00:14:06.638 --> 00:14:09.783
- Are you pregnant?
- Um. not yet.

181
00:14:09.807 --> 00:14:11.995
But I'm afraid I won't be needing
your assistance.

182
00:14:12.019 --> 00:14:13.245
- Take care.
- Oh. no. no. no.

183
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:18.649
That's not why I was looking for you.
I'd like to ask you a question in private.

184
00:14:25.407 --> 00:14:29.327
Oh. I hate that term. "Freedom Day."
So simplistic.

185
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:32.623
"Put Down the Rebellion Day"
would be more accurate.

186
00:14:33.123 --> 00:14:35.209
Ma'am. you said you wanted
to ask me a question.

187
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:39.605
Why'd you do that?

188
00:14:39.629 --> 00:14:41.423
Because I don't want them to hear.

189
00:14:42.006 --> 00:14:43.008
Who?

190
00:14:43.509 --> 00:14:44.967
Well. who's got listeners?

191
00:14:45.844 --> 00:14:46.845
Judicial?

192
00:14:51.682 --> 00:14:56.246
Have you ever wondered
what was on the servers they erased?

193
00:14:56.270 --> 00:15:01.943
In the books they burned?
If it was even the rebels that did it?

194
00:15:03.445 --> 00:15:05.255
- I should get to work.
- Oh. please.

195
00:15:05.279 --> 00:15:06.948
I didn't ask you here on a whim.

196
00:15:08.366 --> 00:15:10.910
I've heard you're someone who also

197
00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:13.120
wonders.

198
00:15:15.706 --> 00:15:16.683
Who told you that?

199
00:15:16.707 --> 00:15:18.644
Why do we live underground?

200
00:15:18.668 --> 00:15:22.213
What actually happened out there?

201
00:15:22.798 --> 00:15:24.674
- I'm going now.
- One last thing.

202
00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:30.054
Do you really think you're the kind of
person they want having children?

203
00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:35.644
[Allison] Three times with no success?

204
00:15:36.227 --> 00:15:39.581
She just said it...
It started to feel a little intentional.

205
00:15:39.605 --> 00:15:43.378
Okay. Now she has officially descended
from eccentric oddball

206
00:15:43.402 --> 00:15:45.028
to completely fucking crazy.

207
00:15:45.696 --> 00:15:46.798
I should send the psych team

208
00:15:46.822 --> 00:15:49.634
- to pay Gloria a visit.
- Don't. She just...

209
00:15:49.658 --> 00:15:52.261
Just what? Said something that upsets you?

210
00:15:52.286 --> 00:15:54.764
She and her husband couldn't have a baby.

211
00:15:54.788 --> 00:15:56.789
She wants you to find out why.

212
00:15:57.290 --> 00:15:59.750
You had your birth control removed. Allie.

213
00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:04.606
We have the same shot at making a baby
as anyone who has clearance.

214
00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:06.400
- [breathes deeply]
- Okay?

215
00:16:06.424 --> 00:16:07.509
Okay.

216
00:16:19.437 --> 00:16:20.748
You're not gonna like this.

217
00:16:20.772 --> 00:16:24.902
Our buddy George submitted another ticket.
Guess whose turn it is to take it.

218
00:16:28.739 --> 00:16:30.758
[sighs deeply]

219
00:16:30.782 --> 00:16:33.677
He's a programmer in the Mids
with a repair stall in the market.

220
00:16:33.701 --> 00:16:36.764
- Why do you have to go?
- Everybody's taking off for Freedom Day.

221
00:16:36.788 --> 00:16:39.933
And because you're working.
I figured I would just be on call.

222
00:16:39.957 --> 00:16:41.936
But he wants me to be there
first thing in the morning.

223
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:44.938
which means I have to go down tonight
and get a room in the hostel.

224
00:16:44.962 --> 00:16:49.927
Also means that we will be missing
this evening's entertainment.

225
00:16:50.844 --> 00:16:51.845
[Holston chuckles]

226
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:55.886
- [whispers] Honey.
- I know. I know. I'll be quiet.

227
00:16:56.557 --> 00:16:58.369
- Not here.
- Yeah. here.

228
00:16:58.393 --> 00:17:00.330
- Honey. Marnes is...
- Let's be quick.

229
00:17:00.354 --> 00:17:01.437
[Holston] Okay.

230
00:17:03.105 --> 00:17:05.084
[Holston moaning]

231
00:17:05.107 --> 00:17:07.211
- [Allison] It's okay. It's okay.
- [objects crashing]

232
00:17:07.236 --> 00:17:10.320
[Allison moaning. breathing heavily]

233
00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:14.928
[thumping]

234
00:17:14.951 --> 00:17:16.618
[chuckles. snorts]

235
00:17:17.246 --> 00:17:18.263
[shushes]

236
00:17:18.288 --> 00:17:21.414
- [Allison moaning]
- [laughs]

237
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:29.358
- [Allison. Holston groaning]
- [clattering]

238
00:17:29.383 --> 00:17:30.984
[both breathing heavily]

239
00:17:31.009 --> 00:17:32.487
- Holy shit.
- [chuckles]

240
00:17:32.510 --> 00:17:36.115
[chuckling] If I don't get pregnant
from that. I never will.

241
00:17:36.138 --> 00:17:37.641
[both chuckling]

242
00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:58.805
[actor 1] We'll beat you to the top
and open the door to the outside.

243
00:17:58.828 --> 00:18:01.682
letting all the poison into the Silo!

244
00:18:01.707 --> 00:18:04.059
- [laughs]
- [children booing]

245
00:18:04.084 --> 00:18:05.394
[actor 2] Not so fast. rebel!

246
00:18:05.419 --> 00:18:09.148
In the name of the Founders! [yells]

247
00:18:09.173 --> 00:18:12.693
- [grunting. yelling]
- [grunting]

248
00:18:12.718 --> 00:18:14.553
- [actor 3 yells]
- [children cheering]

249
00:18:16.846 --> 00:18:18.848
- [band playing music]
- [chattering]

250
00:18:35.240 --> 00:18:37.201
[yells]

251
00:18:40.203 --> 00:18:43.498
- [music continues. louder]
- [chattering continues]

252
00:19:08.231 --> 00:19:09.231
[speaks indistinctly]

253
00:19:22.203 --> 00:19:23.263
[George] Allison Becker?

254
00:19:23.288 --> 00:19:24.516
I am. You must be...

255
00:19:24.539 --> 00:19:27.000
I've been looking forward
to meeting you for a long time.

256
00:19:34.423 --> 00:19:36.861
Sorry about getting you down here
on Freedom Day.

257
00:19:36.884 --> 00:19:39.823
I'm on call. My husband's working. so...

258
00:19:39.846 --> 00:19:41.825
That's what I figured.
him being the sheriff.

259
00:19:41.848 --> 00:19:43.307
Why I thought I might get you.

260
00:19:44.643 --> 00:19:47.688
I don't understand. How can I help you?

261
00:19:48.313 --> 00:19:51.732
[stammers] Yeah. I... I read your post
on how to retrieve deleted files.

262
00:19:52.276 --> 00:19:56.320
I had a feeling it wouldn't stay up long.
so I printed it.

263
00:19:57.573 --> 00:20:00.676
- That must have cost you a fortune.
- Yeah. worth every credit.

264
00:20:00.701 --> 00:20:01.951
It got me a long way.

265
00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:07.182
But I needed to see you in person.
so I put in a repair request

266
00:20:07.207 --> 00:20:08.476
hoping I'd get you.

267
00:20:08.500 --> 00:20:12.063
Of course. they sent everyone but you.
So then I thought with the holiday...

268
00:20:12.086 --> 00:20:13.547
Why didn't you just ask for me?

269
00:20:14.047 --> 00:20:15.590
I didn't wanna arouse suspicion.

270
00:20:16.842 --> 00:20:17.818
From who?

271
00:20:17.843 --> 00:20:19.553
Who wrote the law on relics?

272
00:20:20.304 --> 00:20:22.240
You're worried about Judicial?

273
00:20:22.263 --> 00:20:23.765
[scoffs] Isn't everybody?

274
00:20:25.433 --> 00:20:26.577
Is this about a relic?

275
00:20:26.602 --> 00:20:28.269
That's just it. I don't know.

276
00:20:30.939 --> 00:20:34.067
A guy came in with this

277
00:20:35.027 --> 00:20:36.486
about a year ago.

278
00:20:37.945 --> 00:20:40.781
Said he found it
under the carpet in a closet.

279
00:20:41.909 --> 00:20:44.493
I fired it up. and it...
It looked like it was empty.

280
00:20:45.077 --> 00:20:47.580
Then I tried what you posted...

281
00:20:49.916 --> 00:20:54.712
and I was able to check the memory.

282
00:20:58.799 --> 00:21:03.846
It... It says most of the drive is in use.
but I can't find any files.

283
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:07.993
There's something on there.
I just don't know how to get to it.

284
00:21:08.018 --> 00:21:10.329
Could just be old family recipes.

285
00:21:10.354 --> 00:21:13.523
[scoffs]
Then they're very old family recipes.

286
00:21:14.732 --> 00:21:15.983
I checked the log in IT.

287
00:21:16.817 --> 00:21:18.737
There's no record of this serial number.

288
00:21:19.738 --> 00:21:23.134
Course.
the log starts after the rebellion.

289
00:21:23.157 --> 00:21:25.845
You think this drive
is over 140 years old?

290
00:21:25.868 --> 00:21:28.972
That's impossible. All the drives
were destroyed in the rebellion.

291
00:21:28.997 --> 00:21:30.414
Could just be an entry error.

292
00:21:32.459 --> 00:21:34.627
Or not.

293
00:21:38.548 --> 00:21:42.444
It might be as simple as just figuring out
the name on the directory.

294
00:21:42.469 --> 00:21:43.554
- May I?
- Mmm.

295
00:21:45.096 --> 00:21:46.574
Is there anything I can...

296
00:21:46.597 --> 00:21:48.392
Not talking would be great.

297
00:21:50.644 --> 00:21:53.063
[crowd cheering]

298
00:21:59.862 --> 00:22:02.423
- Happy Freedom Day.
- Happy Freedom Day. Mayor.

299
00:22:02.446 --> 00:22:03.865
Very nice to see you all.

300
00:22:19.714 --> 00:22:20.757
[Allison sighs]

301
00:22:25.887 --> 00:22:28.515
[sniffs. sighs]

302
00:22:32.310 --> 00:22:33.310
[sighs]

303
00:22:36.397 --> 00:22:38.625
Any idea what the 18 means?

304
00:22:38.650 --> 00:22:39.734
Uh-uh.

305
00:22:44.239 --> 00:22:48.367
- Do you have a magnifying glass?
- Um. yep.

306
00:22:54.333 --> 00:22:56.335
[crowd cheering]

307
00:23:07.637 --> 00:23:08.888
[silo leader] Six minutes

308
00:23:09.472 --> 00:23:11.141
and six seconds

309
00:23:11.849 --> 00:23:13.477
past six o'clock

310
00:23:14.144 --> 00:23:15.686
on this day

311
00:23:16.188 --> 00:23:19.625
140 years ago.

312
00:23:19.650 --> 00:23:24.297
That is the moment
we regained our freedom.

313
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:27.592
[crowd cheering]

314
00:23:27.615 --> 00:23:30.786
We are gathered on the anniversary

315
00:23:31.327 --> 00:23:34.080
to remember the terror of the rebellion.

316
00:23:35.123 --> 00:23:36.934
If they had succeeded.

317
00:23:36.959 --> 00:23:40.814
if they had opened the door
to the outside world.

318
00:23:40.837 --> 00:23:44.258
none of us would be here right now.

319
00:23:45.717 --> 00:23:49.739
They didn't succeed. thank the Founders.

320
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:53.451
But they did manage
to take away our history.

321
00:23:53.474 --> 00:23:55.059
Got anything more powerful?

322
00:23:55.685 --> 00:23:57.311
That's as powerful as they get.

323
00:23:59.021 --> 00:24:00.398
It's letters. but...

324
00:24:02.483 --> 00:24:04.152
I think it says "library."

325
00:24:06.613 --> 00:24:09.199
[silo leader]
They destroyed our computer drives.

326
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:16.205
They shredded our files
and burned all the books in our libraries.

327
00:24:22.171 --> 00:24:24.423
Um... [chuckles]

328
00:24:25.007 --> 00:24:26.008
Um...

329
00:24:29.886 --> 00:24:31.930
But they were stopped.

330
00:24:32.556 --> 00:24:36.476
Our heroic forebears won the day.

331
00:24:43.107 --> 00:24:44.442
Look at this. [chuckles]

332
00:24:50.531 --> 00:24:51.991
I won't. [breathing heavily]

333
00:24:52.534 --> 00:24:53.535
You shouldn't either.

334
00:24:54.286 --> 00:24:55.787
You should bury this.

335
00:24:56.371 --> 00:24:58.141
Bury it? Are you kidding?
This is the great...

336
00:24:58.164 --> 00:25:01.435
This is a relic.
It's against the law to even have it.

337
00:25:01.460 --> 00:25:03.770
But this could be the key
to everything we don't know.

338
00:25:03.795 --> 00:25:06.816
- We have to look...
- They can send you out to clean for this.

339
00:25:06.839 --> 00:25:09.759
Are... Are you gonna tell your husband?

340
00:25:10.676 --> 00:25:12.471
Just get rid of it. [breathes shakily]

341
00:25:14.722 --> 00:25:17.934
[door opens. closes]

342
00:25:28.487 --> 00:25:30.381
[breathes heavily]

343
00:25:30.404 --> 00:25:32.615
[silo leader] And their great victory

344
00:25:33.200 --> 00:25:36.721
<i>should be celebrated with cheers.</i>

345
00:25:36.744 --> 00:25:40.207
[crowd cheering]

346
00:25:53.804 --> 00:25:57.741
It should be celebrated with horns.

347
00:25:57.766 --> 00:26:01.310
[crowd blowing horns]

348
00:26:13.198 --> 00:26:14.782
Where the hell does that go?

349
00:26:21.789 --> 00:26:23.458
[horn blowing continues]

350
00:26:28.672 --> 00:26:33.551
And it should be remembered in silence.

351
00:26:55.240 --> 00:26:59.095
[crowd] â™ª Hear the sound that rings â™ª

352
00:26:59.118 --> 00:27:01.806
â™ª It's calling us â™ª

353
00:27:01.829 --> 00:27:05.894
â™ª To our duty â™ª

354
00:27:05.917 --> 00:27:09.396
â™ª Hear the voices sing â™ª

355
00:27:09.421 --> 00:27:12.483
â™ª So loud and proud â™ª

356
00:27:12.508 --> 00:27:16.278
â™ª Praise freedom's beauty â™ª

357
00:27:16.303 --> 00:27:20.491
â™ª See the rising lights â™ª

358
00:27:20.516 --> 00:27:24.244
[singing indistinctly]

359
00:27:24.269 --> 00:27:28.731
â™ª ...Long night. rise up... â™ª

360
00:27:40.035 --> 00:27:42.954
Uh. sorry. Sorry. I'm just...

361
00:27:43.955 --> 00:27:46.083
I'm just really exhausted from that climb.

362
00:27:47.709 --> 00:27:50.878
I think... [sighs] ...if I didn't sit
on my ass all day. I'd be more fit.

363
00:27:51.797 --> 00:27:52.798
Mmm.

364
00:27:53.382 --> 00:27:54.942
- [Allison sighs]
- [Holston] It's okay.

365
00:27:56.801 --> 00:27:58.028
Just saying I'm tired.

366
00:27:58.052 --> 00:27:59.512
[sighs] Yeah.

367
00:28:00.137 --> 00:28:01.138
[sighs]

368
00:28:01.640 --> 00:28:03.535
Are you 70-levels tired.

369
00:28:03.558 --> 00:28:04.643
or are you...

370
00:28:06.769 --> 00:28:07.895
tired?

371
00:28:10.731 --> 00:28:12.025
We still have some time.

372
00:28:12.567 --> 00:28:14.443
This can't be fun for you anymore.

373
00:28:15.278 --> 00:28:16.571
It's not about fun.

374
00:28:19.031 --> 00:28:20.450
I wanna have a baby.

375
00:28:21.285 --> 00:28:24.829
[sighs] So did I.

376
00:28:34.506 --> 00:28:35.632
[Holston sighs]

377
00:28:52.356 --> 00:28:53.636
[Karen] How'd it go with George?

378
00:28:54.817 --> 00:28:55.861
Couldn't help him. [sighs]

379
00:28:56.862 --> 00:28:58.088
I think he's just lonely.

380
00:28:58.113 --> 00:29:00.383
Wants to converse
with other computer geeks.

381
00:29:00.406 --> 00:29:01.490
Hmm.

382
00:29:04.994 --> 00:29:05.971
[sighs]

383
00:29:05.996 --> 00:29:08.724
You know. I don't know
if it's... [sighs] ...something I ate

384
00:29:08.749 --> 00:29:12.019
or if I'm catching a cold.
but I don't feel great.

385
00:29:12.044 --> 00:29:14.003
Then go home. I'll tell Bernard.

386
00:29:15.838 --> 00:29:16.923
Thanks.

387
00:29:19.843 --> 00:29:20.928
Feel better soon.

388
00:29:52.375 --> 00:29:54.086
Oh. Come in. come in.

389
00:29:59.508 --> 00:30:01.551
[sighs] I hoped you'd be back.

390
00:30:02.344 --> 00:30:04.279
Why wouldn't they want us
to have children?

391
00:30:04.304 --> 00:30:05.806
[inhales sharply]

392
00:30:08.933 --> 00:30:12.019
[faucet runs]

393
00:30:18.902 --> 00:30:23.115
- [Holston] Bernard behaving himself?
- I didn't see him.

394
00:30:27.493 --> 00:30:30.306
I think I'm gonna take tomorrow off.
Go to the market.

395
00:30:30.329 --> 00:30:32.642
What do you need? I... I can send a porter.

396
00:30:32.665 --> 00:30:34.710
I just wanna look.

397
00:30:35.210 --> 00:30:36.627
Get some exercise.

398
00:30:37.211 --> 00:30:38.588
Take my mind off...

399
00:30:40.923 --> 00:30:43.443
Sure. Yeah.

400
00:30:43.468 --> 00:30:45.052
Sounds like a good idea.

401
00:31:01.111 --> 00:31:04.489
[door opens. closes]

402
00:31:08.743 --> 00:31:10.119
I wanna see everything.

403
00:31:27.512 --> 00:31:30.057
- [groans] My brain is fried.
- [George chuckles]

404
00:31:30.557 --> 00:31:31.767
[Allison sighs]

405
00:31:35.854 --> 00:31:38.415
Needless to say. we shouldn't tell
anybody about this.

406
00:31:38.440 --> 00:31:40.025
Uh... Needless to say.

407
00:31:40.651 --> 00:31:43.296
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles] When can you come back?

408
00:31:43.319 --> 00:31:44.613
[sighs] I don't know.

409
00:31:50.117 --> 00:31:51.118
What's this?

410
00:31:53.413 --> 00:31:54.580
[George] I don't know.

411
00:31:55.332 --> 00:31:56.333
Last one?

412
00:32:08.470 --> 00:32:11.265
[Allison breathing shakily]

413
00:32:12.015 --> 00:32:12.951
[sighs]

414
00:32:12.976 --> 00:32:15.978
[birds squawking]

415
00:32:27.948 --> 00:32:30.200
- [grunts]
- Hey! Keep right.

416
00:32:38.625 --> 00:32:40.335
[door closes]

417
00:32:55.433 --> 00:32:56.411
It's late.

418
00:32:56.434 --> 00:32:58.538
[inhales sharply] I lost track. [chuckles]

419
00:32:58.561 --> 00:33:02.040
You go on a shopping spree?
Spend all our credits?

420
00:33:02.065 --> 00:33:04.526
[sighs] Oh. yeah. I wish. Next time.

421
00:33:13.201 --> 00:33:14.786
[faucet running]

422
00:33:22.336 --> 00:33:23.503
[faucet turns off]

423
00:33:24.922 --> 00:33:27.192
I got a message from the doctor.

424
00:33:27.215 --> 00:33:29.675
The only time he can see us is at 11:00.

425
00:33:30.760 --> 00:33:35.157
But. uh. you never know.
We technically still have a few hours.

426
00:33:35.182 --> 00:33:36.492
That's fine. [sighs]

427
00:33:36.517 --> 00:33:39.519
I'm gonna sleep in a little.
so I'll meet you there.

428
00:33:45.483 --> 00:33:48.362
Hey. Are you okay?

429
00:33:50.404 --> 00:33:51.405
No.

430
00:33:52.490 --> 00:33:53.700
But I will be.

431
00:33:59.288 --> 00:34:00.289
[Allison sighs]

432
00:34:15.429 --> 00:34:18.516
[clock ticking]

433
00:34:33.197 --> 00:34:34.574
- Hey. Karen.
- Hey.

434
00:34:35.576 --> 00:34:36.577
Where's Allison?

435
00:34:37.244 --> 00:34:41.039
Oh. She sent a note by porter
saying she wasn't feeling well.

436
00:34:43.291 --> 00:34:44.793
- Thanks.
- Sure.

437
00:34:58.139 --> 00:34:59.307
We need to talk.

438
00:35:01.684 --> 00:35:03.186
- What's going on?
- Sit.

439
00:35:06.440 --> 00:35:08.650
- Are you okay?
- Sit. please.

440
00:35:17.576 --> 00:35:18.887
I was gonna talk to you last night.

441
00:35:18.911 --> 00:35:22.496
but I wasn't sure you were gonna
be able to hear what I had to say.

442
00:35:23.623 --> 00:35:25.333
You don't always listen. honey.

443
00:35:26.876 --> 00:35:27.896
What are you talking about?

444
00:35:27.920 --> 00:35:29.922
- I always listen...
- Talking is not listening.

445
00:35:32.257 --> 00:35:37.554
Because you're the lawman.
I figured I needed to give you some proof.

446
00:35:38.847 --> 00:35:41.534
- Proof of what?
- [Allison sighs]

447
00:35:41.557 --> 00:35:43.726
I can't tell you how I know this. but...

448
00:35:45.103 --> 00:35:47.248
they were never gonna
let us have children.

449
00:35:47.271 --> 00:35:49.315
- What?
- We...

450
00:35:51.318 --> 00:35:54.838
I'm not the type of person
they want having kids.

451
00:35:54.862 --> 00:35:56.590
[chuckles] Who... Who's "they"?

452
00:35:56.614 --> 00:35:59.010
The enforcers of the Pact.

453
00:35:59.034 --> 00:36:03.014
They want docile. obedient people.

454
00:36:03.038 --> 00:36:07.768
[stammers] I saw Dr. Leonard
take out your birth control.

455
00:36:07.793 --> 00:36:10.355
- No. you didn't.
- I was there.

456
00:36:10.378 --> 00:36:11.815
He was behind a curtain.

457
00:36:11.838 --> 00:36:13.983
- You didn't see what he was doing.
- Allison...

458
00:36:14.007 --> 00:36:16.217
I can assure you.

459
00:36:17.802 --> 00:36:19.721
he didn't take out my birth control.

460
00:36:20.264 --> 00:36:21.472
How do you know that?

461
00:36:21.974 --> 00:36:23.474
Because I just did.

462
00:36:32.025 --> 00:36:33.277
What did you do?

463
00:36:36.028 --> 00:36:38.407
Keep pressure on it and don't move.

464
00:36:41.492 --> 00:36:42.304
[door closes]

465
00:36:42.327 --> 00:36:43.829
[exhales deeply]

466
00:36:45.621 --> 00:36:48.333
- [panting. groans]
- Hey.

467
00:36:51.460 --> 00:36:53.606
[panting]

468
00:36:53.630 --> 00:36:54.940
- Hey.
- Whoa!

469
00:36:54.965 --> 00:36:57.050
[grunts. panting]

470
00:37:02.054 --> 00:37:03.849
- [people gasp]
- [panting]

471
00:37:07.393 --> 00:37:08.746
- You gotta come.
- [Dr. Leonard] What?

472
00:37:08.769 --> 00:37:10.355
[panting] It's Allison.

473
00:37:10.981 --> 00:37:13.293
- [Marnes] Oh. good. Sheriff!
- I can't. Allison's hurt.

474
00:37:13.317 --> 00:37:14.860
Allison's in the cafeteria.

475
00:37:18.322 --> 00:37:22.409
None of this is real. Do you see?

476
00:37:23.159 --> 00:37:26.014
They wanna keep you in here.
so they're lying to you.

477
00:37:26.038 --> 00:37:29.934
It's green out there. There's green trees.
There's blue skies.

478
00:37:29.958 --> 00:37:33.271
[breathing heavily]
There's things flying in the air.

479
00:37:33.295 --> 00:37:35.713
[breathing heavily]
Is no one listening to me?

480
00:37:36.840 --> 00:37:37.983
They're keeping us here.

481
00:37:38.007 --> 00:37:40.360
- This display is a lie.
- [Holston] Allison.

482
00:37:40.385 --> 00:37:43.530
- Allison. Allison. Come with me.
- They... They want us to... No. no. no. no.

483
00:37:43.554 --> 00:37:44.990
- Listen to me.
- [stammers] We tried...

484
00:37:45.014 --> 00:37:48.286
- We tried three times. I know it's hard.
- I'm not crazy!

485
00:37:48.309 --> 00:37:50.663
- Why are you treating me like I'm crazy?
- Of course not. Of course not.

486
00:37:50.686 --> 00:37:53.583
Allison. I've known several patients
who have had breakdowns.

487
00:37:53.606 --> 00:37:55.960
I'm not having a breakdown.
[laughing. stammering]

488
00:37:55.983 --> 00:37:57.211
[Holston] You are bleeding. honey.

489
00:37:57.235 --> 00:37:59.505
- And you need to come...
- No! [breathes shakily]

490
00:37:59.530 --> 00:38:05.302
No. No. Just... I've been thinking
about this a lot. okay? [sniffles]

491
00:38:05.327 --> 00:38:09.891
Please. [sighs] Just know
there's no other way.

492
00:38:09.914 --> 00:38:13.085
- [Holston breathes shakily]
- I'm sorry. honey.

493
00:38:14.378 --> 00:38:15.878
It's... It's okay.

494
00:38:16.588 --> 00:38:18.440
- It's okay.
- [breathing heavily] I want to go out!

495
00:38:18.465 --> 00:38:20.050
[people gasping]

496
00:38:22.927 --> 00:38:25.137
[crying]

497
00:38:28.684 --> 00:38:31.769
I want to go out. [sighs]

498
00:38:32.436 --> 00:38:33.438
Oh. God.

499
00:38:44.615 --> 00:38:46.344
[crying. breathing heavily]

500
00:38:46.367 --> 00:38:49.079
[handcuffs clicking]

501
00:39:01.340 --> 00:39:03.385
- [Allison crying]
- [Holston exhales heavily]

502
00:39:06.429 --> 00:39:08.740
- [silo leader] There has to be something.
- [Marnes] There isn't.

503
00:39:08.764 --> 00:39:12.954
We could say she was distressed
or that she misspoke or people misheard.

504
00:39:12.978 --> 00:39:16.958
[groans] There were people there.
They heard what they heard.

505
00:39:16.981 --> 00:39:19.460
- Maybe we could...
- We can bribe them. kill them.

506
00:39:19.483 --> 00:39:20.652
No. goddamn it.

507
00:39:21.903 --> 00:39:26.009
The Pact says you can request a hearing
if you feel you have been misheard.

508
00:39:26.032 --> 00:39:28.034
Allison does not feel she was misheard.

509
00:39:28.869 --> 00:39:30.847
Don't you want to at least
look at the possibility?

510
00:39:30.871 --> 00:39:32.414
Of course I do!

511
00:39:33.498 --> 00:39:37.251
Don't you think I've gone over it again
and again? There is nothing I can do.

512
00:39:41.797 --> 00:39:46.135
[inhales deeply] If you boil the Pact
down to one rule.

513
00:39:46.762 --> 00:39:51.474
it's do not say you want to go outside
or you will fucking go outside.

514
00:39:57.271 --> 00:40:01.960
[silo leader] Did anyone else play a part
in this? Steer her in this direction?

515
00:40:01.985 --> 00:40:07.382
She talked to a fertility counselor on 17.
Gloria Hildebrandt.

516
00:40:07.407 --> 00:40:08.967
And what did she say?

517
00:40:08.992 --> 00:40:10.929
She admits she put the bug
in Allison's ear

518
00:40:10.952 --> 00:40:14.056
about us not being the kind
they want having kids.

519
00:40:14.081 --> 00:40:15.224
[silo leader] Who's "they?"

520
00:40:15.248 --> 00:40:16.391
[Holston] She doesn't know.

521
00:40:16.416 --> 00:40:19.436
<i>She's just mad
she and her husband couldn't have kids.</i>

522
00:40:19.460 --> 00:40:21.063
Do your talking at the station.

523
00:40:21.088 --> 00:40:25.275
[Marnes] We also hauled up the guy
from the marketplace. George Wilkins.

524
00:40:25.300 --> 00:40:27.487
<i>He runs a computer repair stall.</i>

525
00:40:27.510 --> 00:40:30.280
<i>Allison gave him tech support
on the holiday.</i>

526
00:40:30.304 --> 00:40:35.744
She went shopping yesterday.
I thought maybe she'd gone to see him.

527
00:40:35.768 --> 00:40:38.521
[Marnes] But Wilkins said
that Allison never came back.

528
00:40:39.231 --> 00:40:43.860
<i>A Judicial team searched his stall.
but they didn't find anything.</i>

529
00:40:45.152 --> 00:40:46.445
[silo leader] Then why?

530
00:40:48.489 --> 00:40:51.117
Allison feels things strongly.

531
00:40:52.994 --> 00:40:55.163
But not being able to have a baby...

532
00:40:57.498 --> 00:41:01.460
I think it was just too much.

533
00:41:05.840 --> 00:41:07.360
[inhales deeply]

534
00:41:07.384 --> 00:41:11.387
Holston. you don't have
to be here for the rest.

535
00:41:12.806 --> 00:41:13.782
I'm the sheriff.

536
00:41:13.806 --> 00:41:15.434
Sure you don't want to step aside?

537
00:41:16.393 --> 00:41:19.329
- I took an oath when I took the job.
- I know. but everyone will...

538
00:41:19.353 --> 00:41:22.858
What's the value of swearing an oath
if you only stick to it when it's easy?

539
00:41:24.943 --> 00:41:25.943
[sighs]

540
00:41:28.864 --> 00:41:30.903
[silo leader]
Two-day holiday. except for essential.

541
00:41:32.034 --> 00:41:34.304
Open rooms Up Top for visitors.

542
00:41:34.327 --> 00:41:38.849
We expect this'll attract a larger crowd
than usual. as it's been a while.

543
00:41:38.873 --> 00:41:42.335
[voice fading] We'll hold a lottery
for attendance in the cafeteria.

544
00:42:00.394 --> 00:42:01.646
[Allison] I'm so sorry.

545
00:42:04.233 --> 00:42:05.233
Me too.

546
00:42:09.445 --> 00:42:10.923
[Allison] I didn't go all crazy.

547
00:42:10.947 --> 00:42:13.242
You cut something out of your body
with a knife.

548
00:42:13.784 --> 00:42:17.579
Yeah. and it hurt like hell. [chuckles]

549
00:42:20.081 --> 00:42:22.309
I took the capsule back to Dr. Leonard.

550
00:42:22.333 --> 00:42:23.769
[Allison] Oh. yeah? What'd he say?

551
00:42:23.793 --> 00:42:27.856
It was in there to hold a spot.
prevent infection.

552
00:42:27.880 --> 00:42:29.132
Something like that. right?

553
00:42:34.429 --> 00:42:35.639
Doesn't matter.

554
00:42:38.141 --> 00:42:42.019
[sighs] I have to tell you something.
[sniffs]

555
00:42:43.271 --> 00:42:44.773
But I need you to sit close.

556
00:42:45.440 --> 00:42:47.668
- I don't want anybody to hear.
- We're alone.

557
00:42:47.693 --> 00:42:49.277
[sighs] Please.

558
00:42:51.320 --> 00:42:52.322
Please.

559
00:43:00.998 --> 00:43:02.039
[sniffles]

560
00:43:03.625 --> 00:43:06.896
[inhales sharply]
First of all. I love you.

561
00:43:06.920 --> 00:43:12.467
- That is the most important thing.
- Is it?

562
00:43:13.050 --> 00:43:16.179
I know you're angry. I would be too.

563
00:43:19.182 --> 00:43:24.164
If I could wind back the clock
and not know what I know. I would.

564
00:43:24.188 --> 00:43:26.398
Ugh. In a heartbeat.

565
00:43:29.483 --> 00:43:33.739
But what I found out.
what they told us isn't true.

566
00:43:34.907 --> 00:43:38.469
Why we're here.
what happened 140 years ago.

567
00:43:38.492 --> 00:43:41.597
why and who gets to have children.
And that's not even the big thing...

568
00:43:41.621 --> 00:43:42.706
So?

569
00:43:43.623 --> 00:43:45.309
- So?
- You find out something like that.

570
00:43:45.333 --> 00:43:49.271
you bring it to me. to Mayor Jahns.
to Judicial.

571
00:43:49.295 --> 00:43:50.856
You let everyone in the Silo know.

572
00:43:50.880 --> 00:43:55.277
What you don't do is say the words
that get you sent out there to die.

573
00:43:55.302 --> 00:44:00.115
But that's the big thing I found out.
I won't die out there.

574
00:44:00.139 --> 00:44:06.079
Listen. they have the ability
to change what we see on the screens.

575
00:44:06.103 --> 00:44:08.500
In the cafeteria.
throughout the Silo. everywhere.

576
00:44:08.523 --> 00:44:10.626
- What are you talking about?
- They take an image.

577
00:44:10.650 --> 00:44:12.545
and... and they alter it somehow.

578
00:44:12.568 --> 00:44:16.840
So. what we see is not what's out there.

579
00:44:16.864 --> 00:44:19.760
It's what they want us
to think is out there.

580
00:44:19.784 --> 00:44:22.012
- What's that? Right there.
- [sighs] Holston.

581
00:44:22.036 --> 00:44:23.306
- And that.
- [Allison sniffles]

582
00:44:23.329 --> 00:44:25.557
[Holston]
The last three people who cleaned.

583
00:44:25.581 --> 00:44:28.376
Or maybe that's not what it is.

584
00:44:28.960 --> 00:44:32.315
- What if it's just rocks and bushes?
- I know what I'm seeing.

585
00:44:32.338 --> 00:44:35.360
Not if it's just
what the computer wants you to see.

586
00:44:35.384 --> 00:44:37.885
- Why would they do that?
- To keep us in here.

587
00:44:39.221 --> 00:44:40.304
Okay. okay.

588
00:44:41.889 --> 00:44:45.686
If it's so wonderful outside.
why would they not want us to go out?

589
00:44:46.436 --> 00:44:47.563
I don't know.

590
00:44:49.690 --> 00:44:52.376
- I don't know.
- O... Okay.

591
00:44:52.400 --> 00:44:55.213
But I'm gonna find out. I'm sorry. [sighs]

592
00:44:55.237 --> 00:44:56.880
- You keep saying that. I... I...
- Okay.

593
00:44:56.905 --> 00:44:59.007
Just one more thing
I want you to think about.

594
00:44:59.032 --> 00:45:00.300
and then you should get some sleep.

595
00:45:00.324 --> 00:45:03.929
- [sighs. cries] Not going anywhere.
- [sighs]

596
00:45:03.954 --> 00:45:07.958
[breathes heavily]
Why do people clean? [sniffles]

597
00:45:09.168 --> 00:45:11.085
[breathes heavily]

598
00:45:12.295 --> 00:45:14.898
To get the dust and grime
off the sensors

599
00:45:14.922 --> 00:45:16.275
- so we can see.
- No. No.

600
00:45:16.300 --> 00:45:18.360
Why do they go through with it?

601
00:45:18.385 --> 00:45:20.155
Most people swear they're not gonna do it.

602
00:45:20.179 --> 00:45:23.115
When you arrested Brent. he said you'd
have to put a bullet through his head

603
00:45:23.139 --> 00:45:25.577
and throw him down the stairs
'cause he wasn't gonna clean.

604
00:45:25.601 --> 00:45:28.829
- And then what did he do?
- He cleaned.

605
00:45:28.853 --> 00:45:32.565
I think people clean
because they hope somehow

606
00:45:33.317 --> 00:45:38.572
that they can show people the truth
that that is a lie.

607
00:45:41.532 --> 00:45:47.164
When I get out there. if that's what
it's really like. I won't clean.

608
00:45:48.664 --> 00:45:51.664
I'll wave goodbye. because I would have
made the biggest mistake of my life.

609
00:45:52.628 --> 00:45:54.713
- But if I'm right...
- [breathes deeply]

610
00:45:55.255 --> 00:45:57.983
and it's green and lush and beautiful.

611
00:45:58.007 --> 00:46:03.597
I'll pull out my wool
and I'll start to clean. And you'll know.

612
00:46:06.141 --> 00:46:10.538
And then I'll walk over the hill.
and I'll find out what's going on.

613
00:46:10.561 --> 00:46:12.356
And then I'll come back for you.

614
00:46:16.025 --> 00:46:17.027
Okay?

615
00:46:35.795 --> 00:46:37.255
[Jahns] "Allison Becker."

616
00:46:38.798 --> 00:46:42.612
You have been charged with
and convicted of violating

617
00:46:42.635 --> 00:46:45.304
the cardinal law of our society.

618
00:46:46.181 --> 00:46:48.891
Any spoken request
to leave the Silo is granted.

619
00:46:50.726 --> 00:46:52.563
but it is irrevocable.

620
00:46:54.815 --> 00:46:58.402
Once uttered. it is determinative.

621
00:47:01.445 --> 00:47:03.114
You have been asked to clean

622
00:47:03.614 --> 00:47:06.409
and have been provided
with materials to do so.

623
00:47:07.244 --> 00:47:09.722
But you cannot be forced into cleaning.

624
00:47:09.746 --> 00:47:14.208
"Once outside the air lock.
you are outside the law."

625
00:47:24.927 --> 00:47:26.054
[sniffs]

626
00:47:27.472 --> 00:47:29.391
"We do not know why we are here."

627
00:47:32.268 --> 00:47:34.478
We do not know who built the Silo.

628
00:47:36.440 --> 00:47:40.360
We do not know why everything
outside the Silo is as it is.

629
00:47:44.655 --> 00:47:46.157
We do not know...

630
00:47:49.286 --> 00:47:51.538
when it will be safe to go outside.

631
00:47:53.664 --> 00:47:55.918
We only know that day is not today.

632
00:47:57.210 --> 00:47:59.378
[cries] Allison Becker.

633
00:48:02.507 --> 00:48:06.637
On behalf of the people of the Silo.
I hope that you will clean

634
00:48:07.429 --> 00:48:12.869
so that we will better see
the world outside our sanctuary as it is

635
00:48:12.893 --> 00:48:15.061
and thereby be reminded

636
00:48:16.063 --> 00:48:20.567
"that here is safe and there is not."

637
00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:23.362
[sighs]

638
00:48:24.905 --> 00:48:26.364
[Holston] Have you any last words?

639
00:48:26.864 --> 00:48:30.744
[breathes deeply] I love you.

640
00:48:34.289 --> 00:48:35.498
I love you.

641
00:49:46.320 --> 00:49:47.653
[door thuds]

642
00:49:55.204 --> 00:49:57.206
[air hissing]

643
00:50:41.750 --> 00:50:45.253
[crowd murmuring]

644
00:51:46.606 --> 00:51:48.400
[crowd cheering]

645
00:51:51.485 --> 00:51:53.280
[crowd whistling. cheering]

646
00:52:46.375 --> 00:52:48.043
[crowd murmuring]

647
00:52:57.760 --> 00:53:00.239
[crowd cheering]

648
00:53:00.264 --> 00:53:01.347
Yes!

649
00:54:36.652 --> 00:54:38.237
[Marnes] Something you should see.

650
00:54:38.737 --> 00:54:42.217
George Wilkins. he's the one Allison
went to help in the marketplace.

651
00:54:42.240 --> 00:54:44.344
- We hauled him up and...
- Yeah. I know who he is.

652
00:54:44.367 --> 00:54:47.204
He got a transfer to Mechanical last year.

653
00:54:48.371 --> 00:54:49.456
Okay.

654
00:54:50.791 --> 00:54:56.563
He's dead. Went over the rail
somewhere around level 120.

655
00:54:56.588 --> 00:54:59.090
Accident? Suicide?

656
00:54:59.842 --> 00:55:00.967
I don't know.

657
00:55:02.594 --> 00:55:05.072
- What does Hank say?
- Eh. He didn't say much.

658
00:55:05.097 --> 00:55:06.722
No one saw him go over.

659
00:55:08.224 --> 00:55:10.393
Get to the part you're not telling me.

660
00:55:11.394 --> 00:55:12.478
[sighs]

661
00:55:13.981 --> 00:55:16.692
There's an engineer down there
that says it's murder.

662
00:55:37.211 --> 00:55:38.755
[Marnes] Where's the engineer?

663
00:55:39.922 --> 00:55:40.923
Uh. she couldn't make it.

664
00:55:41.425 --> 00:55:45.052
It took us a day to walk down here.
She could have cleared her schedule.

665
00:55:45.554 --> 00:55:46.722
Something came up.

666
00:55:52.686 --> 00:55:53.686
Okay.

667
00:56:00.985 --> 00:56:03.338
Meeting with us isn't optional. Hank.

668
00:56:03.362 --> 00:56:06.425
She says this guy was murdered.
We need to speak to her.

669
00:56:06.449 --> 00:56:07.534
What came up?

670
00:56:08.952 --> 00:56:11.246
The generator. It's been giving her fits.

671
00:56:13.164 --> 00:56:14.224
What does she do?

672
00:56:14.248 --> 00:56:16.751
Well. she pretty much keeps everyone
in the Silo alive.

673
00:56:24.717 --> 00:56:27.137
[mechanical whirring. scraping]

674
00:56:41.025 --> 00:56:42.027
[shouting] That's her.

675
00:56:43.445 --> 00:56:44.885
- [shouting] What's her name?
- What?

676
00:56:45.614 --> 00:56:47.132
[shouting] What's her name?

677
00:56:47.157 --> 00:56:49.952
Juliette. Juliette Nichols.

678
00:57:13.724 --> 00:57:15.601
[Marnes] What happened
between you and her?

679
00:57:18.480 --> 00:57:20.858
<i>For two years. you were dead inside.</i>

680
00:57:23.777 --> 00:57:25.528
<i>Then you met Juliette Nichols.</i>

681
00:57:27.030 --> 00:57:30.909
- I finally started listening is all.
- To what?

682
00:57:31.659 --> 00:57:36.123
To Allison.
To what she was trying to tell me.

683
00:57:37.416 --> 00:57:39.309
I'm not gonna tell you what that was.

684
00:57:39.333 --> 00:57:43.630
All you need to know is.
I'm gonna go find her.

685
00:57:45.090 --> 00:57:46.340
You want to find her?

686
00:57:47.259 --> 00:57:49.177
She's right there.

687
00:57:51.972 --> 00:57:53.181
I'm sorry.

688
00:57:55.766 --> 00:57:58.228
As much as I love you. you old bastard.

689
00:57:59.980 --> 00:58:01.481
I love Allison more.

690
00:58:05.777 --> 00:58:10.615
If that really is her out there or not.

691
00:58:11.782 --> 00:58:13.577
either way. I'm done.

692
00:58:14.702 --> 00:58:16.621
I've gotta know the truth.
